= Virtualization Edition Guide for VTN =

To let VTN Manager work correctly in the Virtualization Edition, you have to stop the following bundles.

* arphandler bundle (org.opendaylight.controller.arphandler)
* sample bundles (org.opendaylight.controller.samples.*)
* affinity bundles (org.opendaylight.affinity.*)

To prevent OSGi framework from automatically installing and starting the above bundles,
please edit '''configuration/config.ini''' as follows.

 # Avoid to auto-install following bundles, that means those need
 # to be started manually or in other way like osgi.bundles
 #felix.fileinstall.filter=^(?!org.apache.felix.fileinstall).*
 felix.fileinstall.filter=\
     ^(?!org\\.(apache\\.felix\\.fileinstall|\
                opendaylight\\.(affinity|\
                                controller\\.(arphandler|samples)))).*

You can find '''configuration/config.ini''' under '''opendaylight''' directory (usually the distributions/virtualization/target/distributions-virtualization-0.1.0-SNAPSHOT-osgipackage/'''opendaylight''').

